name: First Sunday Concert Series (#4)
shortDescription: Artists for February are three doctoral candidates: pianists Sichum Gao and Jing Li, and violinist Ziqian Ye.
fullDescription:
Desert Rose Baha’i Institute continues its FIRST SUNDAY CONCERT SERIES at 3pm on
February 1 at Hadden Hall, 1950 West William Sears Dr., Eloy, AZ, featuring world class performers
from the University of Arizona’s School of Music.  Artists for February are three doctoral candidates:
pianists Sichum Gao and Jing Li, and violinist Ziqian Ye.  The pianists will showcase their talents on the
recently acquired and fully restored 1893 A.B. Chase grand piano, demonstrating how the music of
Brahms and Rachmaninoff (compositions used by some therapists to heal the emotional disorder of
depression or melancholy) can lift the soul toward heaven.  Admission is free.
title: First Sunday Concert Series (#4)
